news.title: Madhya Pradesh cabinet allocates Rs 50,000 crore for housing projects for urban poor
news.para: ​Under the Awas Yojana, 10 lakh houses will be constructed in five years to benefit the eligible beneficiary families of economically weaker, lower-and middle-income groups in the urban areas.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh's planning department to soon conduct quarterly audits of EPC projects
news.para: Independent auditors and civil engineers with expertise in examining the structural durability of raw materials and the structure of a building will be deputed to evaluate the quality of a project.

news.title: Hyderabad: HYDRAA conducts two demolition drives in Shamshabad
news.para: One key complaint involved a 998-square-yard public park in Southern Paradise (Sri Sampath Nagar), which was allegedly seized by private parties.

news.title: Over 30 illegal colonies razed, 172 FIRs lodged in Ghaziabad in one year
news.para: "Between Jan 1, 2024, and Jan 17, 2025, GDA carried out anti-encroachment demolition drives across all its eight zones. A total of 87 illegal structures and hutments were razed and over 60,000 sqm of land was reclaimed from land grabbers and secured," a GDA official said.

news.title: Hyderabad: Property worth Rs 150 crore in Jubilee Hills seized in benami transactions case
news.para: The property was registered in Rathi's name in 2017 through two sale deeds of ₹4 crore each, bringing the total sale consideration to ₹8 crore. However, the BPU has estimated the property's current market value to be ₹150 crore.

news.title: Noida: Over 300 employees of Supertech protest over unpaid salary
news.para: Both groups have recently approached the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT), seeking its intervention and an order to interim resolution professional (IRP) Hitesh Goel to clear the dues.

news.title: Greater Noida development body may extend penalty waiver for delays in flats' registries
news.para: Introduced in July 2024 for a six-month period, the waiver has already benefited over 6,500 homebuyers, each receiving a waiver of penalties ranging from Rs 2 lakh to Rs 2.5 lakh.

news.title: Builders can't deduct over 10% of base price in case of cancellation by homebuyers: SC
news.para: A bench of Justices B R Gavai and S V N Bhatt said the contractual terms which are ex facie one-sided, unfair and unreasonable would constitute unfair trade practice.

news.title: Insolvency board issues discussion paper to streamline corporate resolution process
news.para: The paper proposes several amendments to address operational challenges in the resolution framework. The IBBI has invited public comments on the discussion paper till February 25 through its website.

news.title: Birla Corporation's net profit falls 71% to Rs 31 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Birla Corporation's revenue from operations declined 2.32 per cent to Rs 2,256.65 crore during the December quarter. It was Rs 2,310.44 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC to levy property tax on commercial establishments in slums
news.para: BMC commissioner and administrator Bhushan Gagrani said an additional revenue of Rs 350 crore was expected in FY 2025-26 from property tax on shops and other commercial units in slums.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust's net operating income up 6% in Q3 FY25
news.para: The company's Net Operating Income (NOI) rose 6 per cent to Rs 441.6 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal year. Nexus Select Trust is India's first publicly listed retail Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT).

news.title: Sebi penalises DB Realty, promoters, officials for misrepresenting financial statements
news.para: ​The regulator imposed a fine of Rs 5 lakh each on DB Realty Ltd (now known as Valor Estate), Vinod Kumar Goenka (Promoter and Chairperson-MD of DB Realty), and Shahid Balwa Usman (promoter and MD), according to a Sebi order.

news.title: Simpliwork Offices rents 1.5 lakh sq ft workspace in Bengaluru
news.para: Simpliwork Offices CEO and founder Kunal Walia said, "The flexible workspace industry in India is at an inflection point, transitioning from being a disruptor to becoming an integral part of the real estate ecosystem".

news.title: UK: Crest Nicholson warns it may breach loan terms
news.para: Investec analyst Aynsley Lammin said that the firm flagging up the material risk around going concern is an "incremental risk" the market was not expecting.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC presents over Rs 74,000 crore budget for 2025-26
news.para: The additional municipal commissioners presented the budget to BMC Commissioner Bhushan Gagrani, who is the state-appointed administrator of the civic body, at the BMC headquarters here.

news.title: Elan Group to invest Rs 3,000 crore to develop residential project on Dwarka Expressway
news.para: Elan Group's project is a part of the company's over 50 acres township and will comprise of a total of 580 units spread across five towers, with a total saleable area of 28,70,000 sq ft.

news.title: Godrej Properties post net profit of Rs 158.20 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Godrej Properties' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,239.97 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 126.41 per cent from Rs 548.31 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Over 6,000 villages in Nagpur division to undergo drone survey
news.para: Nearly 20% of the villages in Maharashtra covered by the scheme fall under Nagpur division. Of the 8,780 villages in the division, 4,447 have completed their final review, and 5,343 have undergone the inquiry process.

news.title: Bhopal metro phase II will impact one-third less properties than phase I, claims report
news.para: Metro Phase II's 14.14 km blue line metro connecting Bhadbada Square to Ratnagiri is anticipated to commence construction before March's end, according to MPMRCL sources.
